Multiple Interface Implementation
------------------------------------

SYNTAX : 

public class class_name implements interface1,interface2{
    statements....

} 


car                             MediaPlayer
----                            -----------
+turnDirection()                +start
+accelrate()                    +pause
+stop()                         +off
    .                                   .
    .                                   .
    .                                   .
    ......>                      <.......
                    Thar
                    -----
                    +turnDirection()
                    +accelrate()
                    +stop()
                    +start()
                    +pause()
                    +off()

        Thar t1=new Thar()

        Car c=t1;
        MediaPlayer m=t1;

This is multiple interface Implementation.
----------------------------------------------------------------------
NOTE :
--------

--> A class can implements an interface while it is extending another super class [extends & implements].

ex :- 
public class MyClass extends SuperClass implements Iface{

}

extends should come before ( it has 0-100% of abstraction).
interface should come next (it has 100% of abstraction).

--> Interfaces can be extended 

Ex :- 
public interface subInteface extends SuperInteface {

}

--> Intefaces can have member variables
        by default : public , static , final







PACKAGE
--------------------------------------------------------------------
+ Group / Collection of classes
+ If not specified, it is called "Default" package.
+ at top of the java program - package declaration
+ can be accessed by qualifying the package name
            ex : - package.className

